### Describe the bug
Debug breakpoint not hit in OnInitialized method in Razor Class Library from an ASP.NET Core hosted Blazor Client project

### To Reproduce
In [this github repo](https://github.com/mtranchi/DebugBreakNotHitInRazorClassLibrary), set breakpoints on the OnInitialized method as well as on the if statement in the code block of RazorClassLibrary1.Component1:

```
@code{
    string message;

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        message = "OnInitialized breakpoint not hit";

        if (true)
        {
            message += Environment.NewLine + "Neither is the if statement breakpoint hit";
        }

        base.OnInitialized();
    }
}
```
then run the app. The breakpoints won't be hit.


### Further technical details
- ASP.NET Core version 5.0.2
- The IDE: VS 16.8.4

